# Baros Design System Standards

## Mandatory Storybook Stories

Every exported component MUST have a corresponding `ComponentName.stories.tsx` with at least a `Default` story and one story per variant.

## Component API Template

Every Baros component must follow this structure:

```tsx
import { forwardRef, type ComponentPropsWithRef } from 'react';
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';

const buttonVariants = cva('inline-flex items-center justify-center font-medium transition-colors', {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      primary: 'bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700',
      secondary: 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200',
      ghost: 'hover:bg-gray-100',
    },
    size: {
      sm: 'h-8 px-3 text-sm rounded-md',
      md: 'h-10 px-4 text-sm rounded-lg',
      lg: 'h-12 px-6 text-base rounded-lg',
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: 'primary', size: 'md' },
});

interface ButtonProps
  extends Omit<ComponentPropsWithRef<'button'>, 'className'>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
  readonly className?: string;
}

export const Button = forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ variant, size, className, ...props }, ref) => (
    <button ref={ref} className={twMerge(buttonVariants({ variant, size }), className)} {...props} />
  ),
);

Button.displayName = 'Button';
```

## Rules

1. **`forwardRef`** on every component that renders a DOM element.
2. **`className` prop** on every component — merge with `twMerge` so consumers can override.
3. **`cva`** for variant/size props — provides type-safe, consistent variant management.
4. **JSDoc** on all prop interfaces — describe each prop's purpose and valid values.
5. **Sensible defaults** — every variant prop must have a `defaultVariants` entry in `cva`.

## Polymorphic `as` Prop

For components that should render as different HTML elements:

```tsx
interface BoxProps<T extends React.ElementType = 'div'> {
  readonly as?: T;
  readonly className?: string;
  readonly children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Box<T extends React.ElementType = 'div'>({
  as, className, children, ...props
}: BoxProps<T> & Omit<React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<T>, keyof BoxProps<T>>) {
  const Element = as ?? 'div';
  return <Element className={twMerge('', className)} {...props}>{children}</Element>;
}
```

## Compound Components

For complex multi-part components, use the compound pattern:

```tsx
export function Select({ children, ...props }: SelectProps) { ... }
Select.Option = function SelectOption({ ... }: OptionProps) { ... };
Select.Group = function SelectGroup({ ... }: GroupProps) { ... };
```

## Exports

- Every component folder has an `index.ts` barrel export.
- The library root `src/index.ts` re-exports all public components.
- Only consume Tailwind theme tokens — never hardcoded colors or spacing values.
